      <h1>My Skills</h1>
      <ul>
	<li><strong>R: </strong>In school, I used R for the majority of my classwork, whether it was building linear mixed models for my consulting homework or exploratory data analysis with an emphasis on visualization. I primarily use R for EDA, statistical model building using various regression techniques, and statistical diagnostics and inference. Similarly, through my computer science courses I've learned dimensionality reduction techniques and other data mining and classification algorithms.</li>
	
	<li><strong>Python: </strong> In undergrad I was enrolled in a data visualization course, which was taught in Python. We were taught about various data science libraries, such as pandas and numpy. We then visualizated our data using matplotlib, seaborn, and altair.</li>
	
	<li><strong>SQL: </strong> I learned the basics of running and querying databases. For example, I downloaded a  database that includes <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://ergast.com/mrd/db/">data from every Formula 1 racing season</a>. I wrote queries that would export the database into several CSVs, and then visualized my findings in R. Blog post coming soon!</li>
